- `trpc/router.ts` `appRouter` namespaces: `users`, `communities`, `auth`, `config`, `publications`, `comments`, `votes`, `polls`, `wallets`, `notifications`, `search`, `uploads`, `favorites`, `categories`, `about`, `tappalka`, `investments`, `teams`, `platformSettings`, `project`, `ticket`, `platformDev`, `meritTransfer`.
- Sub-router file/export names may differ from the `appRouter` key (e.g. `investmentRouter` from `investment.router.ts` is mounted as `investments`).
- Migration and maintenance scripts also live under `api/scripts/` (outside `api/apps/meriter/src/`); some are wired from `api/package.json` scripts.

### Adding New Backend Feature

**Target flow (post Phase 2‚Äì3):** schema ‚Üí domain service ‚Üí **application use case** ‚Üí thin adapter router ‚Üí shared-types contract.

**Current interim flow:**
1. Add/update schema in `domain/models/[entity]/`; for cross-cutting models, a top-level schema file under `domain/models/` is also used in this codebase
2. Implement business rules in `domain/services/`; orchestration-heavy flows may still live in routers until extracted to `application/use-cases/` (see violation waivers)
3. Register providers/models in `domain.module.ts` (shared domain wiring)
4. Expose via thin tRPC router in `trpc/routers/[entity].router.ts` ‚Äî **do not** add cross-router imports (e.g. `createVoteLogic` from another router); call use case instead when layer exists
5. REST only for auth/bootstrap/passkey/OTP/magic-link; no new REST business endpoints
6. Map responses through canonical `api-v1/common/mappers/entity-mappers.ts` (target: `adapters/mappers/entity-mappers.ts`); attach `ResourcePermissions` via `PermissionRuleEngine` + presenter (target Phase 5)
7. Add/update shared contracts in `libs/shared-types/src/` when shape is cross-package; canonical `ResourcePermissionsSchema` in `schemas.ts` ‚Äî delete `api-v1/common/interfaces/resource-permissions.interface.ts` in Phase 1

