## Canonical enrichment path (API responses)

1. Load domain entities ‚Üí 2. Batch fetch users/communities (`UserEnrichmentService`) ‚Üí 3. `EntityMappers.map*ToApi` ‚Üí 4. Router post-processing (transitional Mongo-only fields) ‚Üí 5. `PermissionRuleEngine` allow/deny (via `PermissionGatesPort` Phase 3+) ‚Üí 6. `permissions.presenter` ‚Üí `ResourcePermissions` + i18n keys only ‚Üí 7. Return shared-types DTO.

## OD-3 permissions split (pending product sign-off)

- **Invariant enforcer:** `PermissionRuleEngine` owns all allow/deny gates (Phase 5 migration from `permissions-helper`)
- **Presenter only:** `permissions.presenter` assembles booleans + i18n disabled-reason keys (`voteDisabled.*`, etc.)
- **Phase 3 interim:** engine stub methods delegate to `PermissionGatesPort`; adapter is sole `permissions-helper` importer
- **Sign-off gate:** `.index/architecture/od3-matrix-signed.yaml` must be product-signed before Phase 5 permissions merge

## Common Mistakes

‚ùå Importing backend runtime code from `api/` in `web/`
‚úÖ Type-only import bridge: `api/apps/meriter/src/trpc/types.ts` re-exports `AppRouter` from `./router`. The web tRPC client imports it from there via a relative path (`web/src/lib/trpc/client.ts`).
‚ùå Duplicating types instead of using shared-types (especially `ResourcePermissions` ‚Äî use `libs/shared-types` only)
‚ùå Domain service importing `trpc/helpers` or `api-v1/*` (V-01; ESLint zone 1‚Äì2 when landed)
‚ùå `PermissionRuleEngine` importing `permissions-helper` ‚Äî use `PermissionGatesPort` + infrastructure adapter
‚ùå Cross-router vote economics (`publications.router` ‚Üí `createVoteLogic`) ‚Äî extract `CreateVoteUseCase` (V-03/V-04)
‚ùå Inline `notificationService.createNotification` in domain services ‚Äî use domain event ‚Üí `NotificationHandlersService` (V-05)
‚öÝÔ∏è Legacy: substantial router orchestration remains until phase-3‚Äì5 extraction; do not add new violations
‚ùå Putting reusable shared components only in `app/` (prefer `features/`, `components/`, or `shared/components`)
